newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds see light nearby trade in afternoon - May 13.
newsitem.headline: European feeds see light nearby trade in afternoon - May 13.

text.p: Business on the European meals and feeds market picked up this afternoon on calls for a stronger Chicago soymeal futures opening and a dip in the dollar, market sources said.
"Turnover was not big but at least we saw some action, mostly nearby material, on a dip in the dollar and expectations Chicago futures would open a bit higher," one broker said.

Buyers were cautiously attracted by sharply weaker prices in soymeal pellets, which followed last nights sharply lower Chicago soymeal futures close after USDA surprisingly left 1996/96 U.S. soybean ending stocks unchanged at 125 million bushels.
